## 4. MULTI-TENANT PATTERN

### 4.1 Strategy

Every data query is scoped to `institute_id`. The `InstituteHelper` provides the current tenant context throughout the app.

### 4.2 InstituteHelper

```php
// app/Helpers/InstituteHelper.php

class InstituteHelper
{
    public static function current(): ?Institute
    {
        if (!auth()->check()) return null;
        return auth()->user()->institute;
    }
    
    public static function id(): ?int
    {
        return auth()->user()?->institute_id;
    }
    
    public static function name(): string
    {
        return self::current()?->name ?? 'Vidya';
    }
    
    public static function logo(): ?string
    {
        $logo = self::current()?->logo_path;
        return $logo ? asset('storage/'.$logo).'?v='.time() : null;
    }
}
```

### 4.3 Global Scoping Middleware

```php
// app/Http/Middleware/ScopeToInstitute.php

public function handle($request, Closure $next)
{
    if (auth()->check()) {
        $instituteId = auth()->user()->institute_id;
        
        // Apply global scope via View::share
        View::share('currentInstitute', InstituteHelper::current());
        View::share('instituteName', InstituteHelper::name());
        View::share('instituteLogo', InstituteHelper::logo());
    }
    
    return $next($request);
}
```

### 4.4 Query Pattern Example

```php
// ALWAYS scope queries to institute_id

// ❌ WRONG (security risk):
$students = Student::where('batch_id', $batchId)->get();

// ✅ CORRECT:
$students = Student::where('institute_id', InstituteHelper::id())
    ->where('batch_id', $batchId)
    ->get();

// OR use Eloquent global scope (better):
// In Student model:
protected static function booted()
{
    static::addGlobalScope('institute', function ($query) {
        if (auth()->check()) {
            $query->where('institute_id', auth()->user()->institute_id);
        }
    });
}
```

