## 14. MASTERY CALCULATION ENGINE

### 14.1 MasteryCalculationService

```php
class MasteryCalculationService
{
    public function updateForTest(int $testId): void
    {
        $test = Test::find($testId);
        $studentIds = StudentResponse::where('test_id', $testId)
            ->distinct('student_id')
            ->pluck('student_id');
        
        foreach ($studentIds as $studentId) {
            $this->updateStudentMastery($studentId, $testId);
        }
    }
    
    private function updateStudentMastery(int $studentId, int $testId): void
    {
        // Get all responses for this student in this test
        // Group by curriculum_node_id (subtopic)
        $responsesBySubtopic = StudentResponse::with('testQuestion')
            ->where('student_id', $studentId)
            ->where('test_id', $testId)
            ->get()
            ->groupBy('testQuestion.curriculum_node_id');
        
        foreach ($responsesBySubtopic as $subtopicId => $responses) {
            // Calculate cumulative mastery
            $existing = StudentSubtopicMastery::firstOrNew([
                'student_id' => $studentId,
                'curriculum_node_id' => $subtopicId,
            ]);
            
            $newAttempted = $responses->count();
            $newCorrect = $responses->where('is_correct', true)->count();
            $newMarksEarned = $responses->sum('marks_awarded');
            $newMarksPossible = $responses->sum(function($r) {
                return $r->testQuestion->correct_marks ?? 4;
            });
            
            // Update cumulative
            $existing->total_questions_attempted += $newAttempted;
            $existing->total_questions_correct += $newCorrect;
            $existing->total_marks_earned += $newMarksEarned;
            $existing->total_marks_possible += $newMarksPossible;
            
            // Recalculate percentages
            if ($existing->total_questions_attempted > 0) {
                $existing->mastery_percentage = 
                    ($existing->total_questions_correct / $existing->total_questions_attempted) * 100;
            }
            if ($existing->total_marks_possible > 0) {
                $existing->accuracy_percentage = 
                    ($existing->total_marks_earned / $existing->total_marks_possible) * 100;
            }
            
            // Track last test
            $existing->last_test_score = $newMarksEarned;
            $existing->last_updated_at = now();
            
            $existing->save();
        }
    }
}
```

### 14.2 Mastery Formula

```
Subtopic Mastery % = (Total Correct ÷ Total Attempted) × 100

Accuracy % = (Total Marks Earned ÷ Total Marks Possible) × 100
  (differs from mastery when negative marking applies)

Example:
  Student attempted 10 questions of "Kinematics" across 5 tests
  Got 7 correct, 2 wrong, 1 skipped
  
  Mastery: 7/10 × 100 = 70%
  Marks: +4×7 + (-1×2) + 0×1 = 28 - 2 = 26
  Possible: 4×10 = 40
  Accuracy: 26/40 × 100 = 65%
  
  Both tracked — mastery for conceptual clarity, accuracy for exam performance.
```

